  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response in Cox&apos;s Bazar, Bangladesh, Focusing on the Urgent Needs to Support the People Affected by the Tragic Fire on 22 March 2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM focuses on ensuring the effective, sufficient, and equitable provision of life-saving participatory water, sanitation and hygiene services to the most vulnerable individuals in the Rohingya camps and surrounding host communities in Bangladesh. Additionally it provides safe and dignified living conditions to reduce suffering and increase resilience and provide life-saving emergency Shelter/non-food item support to households affected by the disaster for refugees and the host community living adjacent to camps; and is providing the asset replacement and livelihoods support to the affected host communities and self-reliance support to the affected refugees as well as on strengthening security for both refugees and host communities in the affected camps.</narrative>
  </description>
